Date: Thu 13 Nov 2003
From: Phil Mamer <drpmm@rmci.net>

We actually do have a licensed alligator farm in Idaho. They are raised in
closed houses in geothermal water on a tilapia and catfish farm, also
raised in geothermal water. The alligators are imported to Idaho as
hatchlings from Florida and are used as a waste disposal system for the
fish farm and fish processing plant disposing of morts and offal. They are
raised to about 3 to 4 feet then processed for their hides and meat. They
were legally imported with permits from USFWS, Idaho State Department of
Agriculture, and Idaho Fish and Game.
--
Phil Mamer DVM
Wildlife Veterinarian
Idaho Fish and Game
Wildlife Health Laboratory
16569 South 10th
Caldwell, Idaho 83607
<drpmm@rmci.net>
